WEBVTT

00:02.169 --> 00:03.504
NARRATOR:
<i>Previously on</i> The Vampire Diaries:

00:03.671 --> 00:04.714
The cure to vampirism.

00:04.880 --> 00:07.091
You're going to take it,
and I'll take it with you.

00:07.258 --> 00:11.470
I can't let you do this before you've let
everyone in your life try to talk you out of it.

00:11.637 --> 00:12.917
- I'm pregnant.
ALARIC: Marry me.

00:13.055 --> 00:14.098
Yes.

00:14.265 --> 00:17.184
If my life is gonna fall apart
when my humanity starts flooding back...

00:17.351 --> 00:18.394
...then so is yours.

00:18.602 --> 00:21.647
I tried to kill you,
and then I made you turn it off.

00:21.856 --> 00:23.566
I ruined everything.

00:23.774 --> 00:26.235
Before the 1900s, Lily fell in
with a group of witches...

00:26.402 --> 00:28.237
...that were cast out of the Gemini Coven.

00:28.404 --> 00:30.906
Heretics are ruthless.
Vampires with witch power.

00:31.115 --> 00:35.494
- They can never be allowed to escape.
- It's time we get the hell out of this place.

00:35.703 --> 00:37.496
You went off the deep end last night.

00:38.122 --> 00:39.665
[ALL GASP]

00:39.832 --> 00:40.958
I'm a mess.

00:41.625 --> 00:43.252
[BOTH GRUNT]

00:44.628 --> 00:46.964
You have no idea
what devastation feels like.

00:47.131 --> 00:48.883
But you will.

00:51.427 --> 00:53.429
[WHIMPERING]

01:06.525 --> 01:07.651
Elena?

01:36.138 --> 01:38.974
- Hello again, Bonnie.
- Lily.

01:39.141 --> 01:43.020
- I thought Stefan locked you in the cellar.
- He did. But prisons are easily escaped.

01:43.187 --> 01:45.064
- You should know that.
- What do you want?

01:45.397 --> 01:49.568
Must I constantly repeat myself?
If you don't know what I want by now...

01:49.735 --> 01:52.363
You want your creepy
witch-vampire family back.

01:52.738 --> 01:55.157
At the risk of repeating myself,
there's no way.

01:55.324 --> 01:56.367
Isn't there?

01:56.534 --> 01:59.995
What's that term you witches
are so fond of? "Loophole"?

02:00.162 --> 02:04.375
Mm. Even if there is a loophole,
I wouldn't help you find it.

02:04.542 --> 02:06.168
You've made your position clear.

02:06.335 --> 02:10.339
Apparently I've failed to do the same. You
seem to think that I'm here for your help.

02:10.881 --> 02:12.716
I'm not.

02:13.717 --> 02:15.594
[SPEAKS INCANTATION]

02:16.178 --> 02:18.889
Heh. Those are lovely words, Bonnie.

02:19.056 --> 02:21.016
Here's another one: Die.

02:21.684 --> 02:22.726
[GRUNTING]

02:30.818 --> 02:33.154
Wow. You are not good at running.

02:34.697 --> 02:36.323
[SPEAKS INCANTATION]

02:36.532 --> 02:39.326
No magic? Oh, that's my fault.
I was spooning you earlier.

02:39.493 --> 02:40.953
I might've sleep-siphoned you.

02:41.120 --> 02:44.707
Oh, but keep trying. It's adorable.
Like you're having a little seizure.

02:44.874 --> 02:47.585
- How are...?
- Think you could keep screwing people over...

02:47.751 --> 02:50.671
...and there wouldn't be any
consequences? LILY: Now...

02:51.547 --> 02:53.424
...where were we?

02:54.216 --> 02:56.969
Up, up, up. Come on. No time to sleep in.
We have to get Jo.

02:57.178 --> 02:58.721
- Get Jo?
- Yeah.

02:58.929 --> 03:00.014
Is everything okay?

03:00.222 --> 03:03.976
I hope so, considering she's walking down
the aisle in T-minus-10 hours.

03:04.185 --> 03:07.021
Come on. Wedding bells await.

03:15.529 --> 03:17.156
Crap.

03:17.823 --> 03:18.949
They're not here.

03:19.158 --> 03:20.659
- What's wrong?
- My shoes.

03:20.868 --> 03:23.621
My gorgeous, expensive, wear-them-once-
and-then-never-again shoes...

03:23.787 --> 03:24.830
...they are missing.

03:25.039 --> 03:27.159
- Do you want me to do a locator spell?
- On my shoes?

03:27.208 --> 03:28.528
BONNIE: Mm-hm.
- Is that possible?

03:28.626 --> 03:30.085
I don't know, actually. I'm just...

03:30.252 --> 03:33.297
Hang on. I gotta figure out
how to work this stupid thing.

03:33.505 --> 03:37.551
Good, break it. Because my wrinkled dress
will distract everyone from my bare feet.

03:37.760 --> 03:40.596
Hey, hey.
Come on, don't waste all your panic now.

03:40.804 --> 03:44.350
You still have eight hours until
the ceremony. Nonalcoholic mimosa?

03:44.516 --> 03:47.353
One, a nonalcoholic mimosa is just juice.
Two, I can't drink.

03:47.519 --> 03:50.773
- Somebody should drink. You should drink.
- I will drink, eventually.

03:50.981 --> 03:55.819
But I have human tolerance now, which
is cheaper, but a lot less fun. Cheers.

03:55.986 --> 03:57.112
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

03:57.279 --> 03:59.031
JO: Mm.
- Oh. No, no, no.

04:00.366 --> 04:02.451
- Relax.
- H oo.

04:02.618 --> 04:04.036
Jo's phone.

04:04.578 --> 04:06.163
Oh. Huh.

04:06.330 --> 04:08.832
- Uh, okay.
- That's not an "okay" okay.

04:09.833 --> 04:13.712
- That's a "there's a problem" okay.
- Yeah, we'll call you back. Okay, bye.

04:14.255 --> 04:15.798
Danielle's got the flu.

04:15.965 --> 04:17.173
[CHUCKLES]

04:17.341 --> 04:20.052
It sounded like you just said
"Danielle has the flu."

04:20.302 --> 04:23.681
Which is impossible because
Danielle is my wedding coordinator.

04:23.847 --> 04:27.059
- Yeah.
- Well, how sick is she? Can she still work?

04:27.226 --> 04:30.145
It depends on how much vomit
you wanna have at the wedding.

04:30.312 --> 04:31.772
[JO SIGHS]

04:31.939 --> 04:34.024
CAROLINE:
To be honest, maybe this is a good thing.

04:34.191 --> 04:37.528
Because no matter how good Danielle was,
I'm pretty sure I'm better.

04:39.947 --> 04:42.116
Caroline. I missed you.

04:42.324 --> 04:43.867
I missed me too.

04:45.035 --> 04:46.704
Thank you for getting me back.

04:49.248 --> 04:51.375
- H i.
- H i.

04:53.085 --> 04:56.880
Heh. Okay. Now, we got a lot to do
and not a lot of time to do it.

04:57.047 --> 04:59.091
Have a drink. You're not going to pass out.

04:59.258 --> 05:02.886
Bonnie, the switch is on the left-hand side
on the back.

05:03.053 --> 05:04.138
- Oh.
- And, Jo...

05:04.305 --> 05:06.056
...I can see your shoes under the couch.

05:06.890 --> 05:09.184
Okay. Now, who's dealing with the boys?

05:09.393 --> 05:11.020
Okay, we got suits.

05:11.228 --> 05:13.188
I got the rings.

05:13.397 --> 05:15.399
And the vows.

05:15.607 --> 05:18.569
So, what do we do now?

05:18.777 --> 05:20.029
TYLER:
To Alaric Saltzman...

05:20.237 --> 05:23.949
...who, after today, will have sex with
only one woman for the rest of his life.

05:24.283 --> 05:26.410
Seriously, one. You can't look after this.

05:26.577 --> 05:30.122
Not that chicks are throwing themselves
at an occult studies professor, but...

05:30.331 --> 05:32.207
You should lock this down while you can.

05:32.374 --> 05:34.418
Remember how great it was
when you were fighting?

05:34.585 --> 05:37.296
Sorry, full moon tonight.
Feeling extra dickish.

05:37.463 --> 05:39.089
And what's your excuse?

05:39.256 --> 05:40.382
[CELL PHONES BUZZ AND CHIME]

05:40.549 --> 05:42.259
What? What is it?

05:43.093 --> 05:44.303
Wedding-day chores.

05:44.470 --> 05:45.763
BOTH:
Courtesy of Caroline.

05:45.929 --> 05:48.265
Karma. Sweet, sweet karma.

05:48.432 --> 05:49.933
[ALL CHUCKLE]

05:51.769 --> 05:55.939
Okay, the boys are officially taken care of,
bride and maid of honor in hair and makeup.

05:56.106 --> 05:58.275
I'm gonna head to the venue
and fix whatever they're screwing up.

05:58.442 --> 06:00.944
- Elena, the curling iron, just...
- Yes, I see it, Care.

06:01.111 --> 06:03.030
- Okay.
- I'm human now, not blind.

06:03.197 --> 06:05.991
I'm not fragile either. You don't
have to walk on eggshells around me.

06:06.158 --> 06:08.369
I do, actually,
because if you walked on them...

06:08.535 --> 06:10.954
...they could cut you,
you'd get infected and die.

06:11.455 --> 06:15.334
You know what? Given my luck,
that actually seems possible.

06:15.501 --> 06:16.960
[BOTH LAUGH]

06:17.461 --> 06:20.881
So, what's it like now
in the world of the living?

06:21.090 --> 06:23.175
It's different. I'm slower.

06:23.384 --> 06:25.803
I have to look both ways
before crossing the street.

06:26.011 --> 06:28.514
- But it's nice to not...
- Be a monster like me...

06:28.680 --> 06:30.766
...who turns off their humanity
and commits murder...

06:30.933 --> 06:33.185
...instead of dealing with grief
like a normal person?

06:33.352 --> 06:35.854
I was gonna say
not to have to wear a daylight ring.

06:36.021 --> 06:37.606
[CAROLINE SIGHS]

06:38.315 --> 06:39.817
Look, I'm so sorry, Elena.

06:40.025 --> 06:41.360
I was trying to hurt you...

06:41.527 --> 06:45.155
...when I said you would never be happy
with Damon because you weren't human.

06:45.322 --> 06:46.824
And now you are.

06:46.990 --> 06:51.578
I just hope it's not because I made you think
that you would be miserable for eternity.

06:51.745 --> 06:55.541
Care, I've wanted to be human
from the day I became a vampire.

06:55.958 --> 06:59.461
Besides, I'm the last person
that you need to apologize to.

07:00.295 --> 07:03.632
Thanks. I kind of wanted to start
with an easy one. Heh.

07:04.091 --> 07:06.427
- The dreaded amends tour.
- Mm.

07:06.593 --> 07:09.012
If you see Stefan, by
the way, I'm avoiding.

07:09.179 --> 07:11.390
I just need to get my life in order first.

07:11.557 --> 07:13.267
Starting with my friends.

07:13.434 --> 07:15.018
Stefan is not a friend?

07:15.310 --> 07:18.021
Stefan's complicated.

07:18.188 --> 07:20.315
I just figured I'd work
my way up to that one.

07:20.482 --> 07:23.360
You're in the clear.
He's got his hands full with Damon today.

07:23.527 --> 07:24.695
What's wrong with Damon?

07:24.862 --> 07:28.198
Not much. He just said he
would take the cure with me.

07:29.700 --> 07:32.202
Damon Salvatore? Human?

07:33.871 --> 07:35.205
I can't even picture it.

07:35.372 --> 07:39.710
Yeah. Something tells me neither can he.

07:40.377 --> 07:44.256
Sure, I'll be your best man, Ric.
But first, hang out with the worst men...

07:44.465 --> 07:47.217
...so my brother can kidnap me
on the day of your wedding.

07:47.384 --> 07:49.219
Hey, don't you hate weddings anyway?

07:49.428 --> 07:52.639
- I hate little Stefan mind games even more.
- Heh.

07:53.390 --> 07:57.019
So any time you wanna clue me in
as to where the hell we're going...

07:57.227 --> 07:59.563
Oh, come on.
It's your last few days as a vampire.

07:59.771 --> 08:02.608
You can't blame me
for wanting to spend time with my brother.

08:02.816 --> 08:05.068
Oh, look, here we are.

08:13.160 --> 08:15.746
Is Mr. Rogers expecting us?

08:15.954 --> 08:17.623
You know Mr. Rogers is dead, right?

08:17.831 --> 08:21.752
You're gonna be joining him in Make-Believe
if you don't get to the damn point.

08:21.960 --> 08:27.090
So this is a house I lived in during
one of my many attempts to start over.

08:28.342 --> 08:30.135
Welcome to your suburban nightmare.

08:30.469 --> 08:34.181
- Don't think I've thought this through?
- You've thought about a life with Elena.

08:34.347 --> 08:37.476
I don't think you've thought about
neighbors or a mortgage or...

08:37.683 --> 08:38.852
BOY:
Hey!

08:41.355 --> 08:42.523
Or kids.

08:42.731 --> 08:45.275
I don't know. Might not be your thing.

08:54.284 --> 08:56.578
Relax. Relax.

08:56.745 --> 09:00.290
- I'm not here to cause mischief.
- Said everyone who ever causes mischief.

09:00.457 --> 09:03.919
- I told Lily I'd visit.
- Is this like some Oedipus thing or...?

09:04.086 --> 09:06.004
You know what? Doesn't matter.

09:06.171 --> 09:07.965
Excuse me, little witch.

09:08.131 --> 09:10.259
If you think I'm gonna let you,
a ruiner, in here...

09:10.425 --> 09:13.804
...to see another ruiner on the day of Jo's
wedding, you got another thing coming.

09:14.012 --> 09:17.015
- She's lonely and hungry.
- And she can't eat that.

09:17.224 --> 09:20.644
I'm not trying to feed her.
I'm trying to keep her sane.

09:21.520 --> 09:25.023
That is filled with loads of songs
from the last era she knew.

09:25.190 --> 09:27.109
I thought it might bring her comfort.

09:27.317 --> 09:31.446
If you're not a complete monster,
I trust you'll pass it on.

09:37.953 --> 09:40.122
LILY:
I want my family back.

09:40.330 --> 09:41.790
That's all I've ever wanted.

09:41.999 --> 09:45.752
To have my family back with me,
where they belong.

09:49.840 --> 09:51.341
What?

09:55.637 --> 09:56.847
[GASPS]

09:59.224 --> 10:00.726
[GRUNTS]

10:11.028 --> 10:14.740
She was rambling on about her family,
and I got close to her and she attacked me.

10:14.906 --> 10:16.033
Like an animal.

10:16.199 --> 10:19.202
Sounds like she's reached
the full-blown crazy stage of drying out.

10:19.369 --> 10:21.663
You're saying
this is because she's drying out?

10:21.830 --> 10:24.666
It's hard for me to explain
how awful it is, but, yeah.

10:24.833 --> 10:28.795
Your mind starts playing tricks on you.
You start seeing things and people.

10:28.962 --> 10:30.922
What happens when the crazy stage is over?

10:31.089 --> 10:33.717
Stefan said that he has a plan
to get her back on track.

10:33.925 --> 10:37.888
Does that plan involve letting her out? If
he thinks she's giving up on her family...

10:38.055 --> 10:40.891
She has to. Bonnie, you already destroyed
the ascendant.

10:41.058 --> 10:42.893
What if there's a loophole?

10:43.060 --> 10:44.394
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACH]

10:44.936 --> 10:48.774
I'm dreading it, but I guess
I should think about putting the dress on.

10:49.816 --> 10:53.820
Something's wrong. It's not the dress,
is it? Tell me it's not the dress.

10:53.987 --> 10:56.406
We were discussing the fact
that there's a vampire...

10:56.573 --> 10:59.284
...locked in a cell 50 feet
from where we're getting ready.

10:59.451 --> 11:02.788
- Did she do something to the dress?
- Dress is fine. I'm being paranoid.

11:03.288 --> 11:05.540
Okay, truck's here. Who's coming?

11:06.583 --> 11:09.753
Caroline suggested in a semithreatening way
I pick up the centerpieces...

11:09.920 --> 11:11.963
...which sounds like a screw-up
waiting to happen.

11:12.130 --> 11:13.173
I'll come.

11:13.423 --> 11:14.966
- Thank you.
BONNIE: Yeah.

11:15.592 --> 11:17.260
CAROLINE:
<i>No, not there. There.</i>

11:17.469 --> 11:18.929
Just a little bit higher.

11:19.137 --> 11:20.681
Well, that's not a little, but...

11:20.931 --> 11:23.600
But I'm bad at flowers?
Yeah. I assumed you knew that.

11:24.935 --> 11:27.145
Caroline, why am I here?

11:31.942 --> 11:35.445
I tried to kill you. My humanity was off,
but I still tried to kill you.

11:35.612 --> 11:38.615
And you're my friend and I'm sorry.

11:39.074 --> 11:40.784
It's funny.

11:41.201 --> 11:45.497
You and I moved on a while ago, but getting
tortured by your ex and her new boyfriend...

11:45.706 --> 11:47.290
...is never good for the ego.

11:47.499 --> 11:48.875
He's not my boyfriend.

11:49.126 --> 11:50.627
Whatever he is, I can't keep up.

11:50.836 --> 11:53.588
You have to know I would never do
anything like that if it weren't...

11:53.755 --> 11:55.632
You're good, Care.

11:55.841 --> 11:58.281
And if you wanna make amends,
let me get the hell out of here.

11:58.385 --> 11:59.594
[LAUGHS]

11:59.761 --> 12:02.723
Nice try. If I were getting married
at an altar that looked like that...

12:02.889 --> 12:04.141
...I'd be divorced in a week.

12:04.349 --> 12:06.643
So come on, Lockwood, next row.

12:06.852 --> 12:09.730
Honestly, you should probably
do that yourself.

12:09.980 --> 12:11.690
Liv. What are you doing here?

12:11.898 --> 12:13.942
You do know that Jo is my sister, right?

12:15.152 --> 12:16.486
Goody, more amends.

12:16.695 --> 12:19.364
Drinks will help. Strong ones.

12:20.866 --> 12:23.827
- You look good.
- Thanks.

12:23.994 --> 12:26.329
- How are things?
- Good.

12:26.538 --> 12:29.499
- Still recovering from that injury?
- What injury?

12:29.708 --> 12:32.210
Whatever injury turned you
into a monosyllabic goon.

12:32.419 --> 12:33.837
Monosyllabic.

12:34.045 --> 12:36.339
That's an awfully big word
for a college dropout.

12:36.548 --> 12:38.717
I'm sorry.
Was I supposed to stay at Whitmore?

12:38.925 --> 12:42.512
After my ass of a boyfriend told me
he never wanted to see me again?

12:42.721 --> 12:46.308
- You're mad at me?
- I lost my brother and my boyfriend in a week.

12:46.475 --> 12:48.852
Instead of coming to me,
you tried to kill yourself.

12:49.019 --> 12:50.979
- I was hurt.
- That doesn't make it okay.

12:51.146 --> 12:53.398
You're lecturing me on
flying off the handle?

12:53.565 --> 12:55.066
Wow.

12:55.233 --> 12:57.736
You know what? I'm gonna wait outside.

12:57.944 --> 13:01.198
Gemini wedding means
big coven reunion heading this way.

13:06.703 --> 13:07.829
[SIGHS]

13:12.417 --> 13:15.378
Elena said she's desiccating
and that's why she's crazy, but...

13:15.587 --> 13:17.255
Yeah.

13:17.964 --> 13:20.425
She killed two people
when she wasn't desiccating.

13:20.675 --> 13:25.013
I know this will sound crazy, but I've been
having these nightmares with her and Kai.

13:29.726 --> 13:32.187
- Here.
- What's this?

13:32.896 --> 13:36.525
When Bonnie Bennett has a hunch,
you don't ignore it.

13:37.692 --> 13:39.945
- What should we do?
- I know what we shouldn't do.

13:40.111 --> 13:42.906
Leave her in the hands
of two people we don't trust.

13:43.573 --> 13:44.908
Yeah, it's nice.

13:45.116 --> 13:48.203
Brazilian hardwoods, open floor plan...

13:48.370 --> 13:50.205
...updated kitchen.

13:50.372 --> 13:51.581
[MICROWAVE HUMMING]

13:51.748 --> 13:53.917
What kind of roadkill
are you cooking in there?

13:54.084 --> 13:57.087
Considering the fact
that you actually have to eat as a human...

13:57.254 --> 14:00.340
...I wanted to give you a taste
of what your dinner will look like.

14:01.258 --> 14:03.093
You don't cook, Elena doesn't cook.

14:03.260 --> 14:06.263
Who has time anyway
with work and kids, right?

14:07.889 --> 14:14.145
Mm. Salisbury steak. Dig in, Damon. You're
gonna need all that energy for these.

14:14.396 --> 14:15.772
Oh, yeah? What's this?

14:16.940 --> 14:20.110
- It's just the rest of your life.
- Paperwork? That's your big move?

14:20.318 --> 14:22.988
When's the last time
you filled out paperwork of any kind?

14:23.154 --> 14:25.782
Taxes, health insurance, driver's license?

14:25.949 --> 14:28.994
Every idiot in the country does it.
You think I'll have trouble?

14:29.244 --> 14:32.163
You will the first time you encounter
some moron you can't kill.

14:32.372 --> 14:34.457
Maybe, but then I'll just come home...

14:34.666 --> 14:38.628
...and pop a beer from my beautiful
stainless steel refrigerator.

14:38.795 --> 14:41.464
Which you won't be able to afford
unless you have a job.

14:41.631 --> 14:44.801
And if you were about to say
you can borrow money from me, you can't.

14:44.968 --> 14:48.305
- That's not very brotherly of you.
- It is. I won't know where you live.

14:48.471 --> 14:50.682
You'll have the cure
running through your veins.

14:50.849 --> 14:54.269
And if I know where you are,
somebody can use me to track you down...

14:54.477 --> 14:58.189
...take the cure from you
and turn you into a 172-year-old corpse.

14:58.648 --> 15:00.942
What's the matter?
Haven't thought that far ahead?

15:01.109 --> 15:05.530
See, eventually word will spread,
and you and Elena will have to move away.

15:05.697 --> 15:09.784
You'll have to isolate yourself.
No friends, no family.

15:09.951 --> 15:11.912
This will be your life, Damon.

15:12.203 --> 15:14.831
This will be your hell.

15:16.917 --> 15:20.962
Well, that is where
you're wrong, my brother.

15:22.005 --> 15:24.382
This will not be my life.

15:25.592 --> 15:27.135
This will be my life.

15:27.302 --> 15:29.471
See, Elena was explicit
about what she wanted.

15:29.638 --> 15:31.848
This isn't TriBeCa... New
York's too crowded.

15:32.182 --> 15:36.645
...but it is above a bar that I own
next to a medical school.

15:36.811 --> 15:38.355
It's in the northwest somewhere.

15:38.521 --> 15:42.317
I'd tell you where it was, but you've
made it clear you didn't wanna know.

15:45.028 --> 15:47.197
I'm gonna go check out upstairs.

15:47.364 --> 15:49.366
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

15:52.202 --> 15:55.205
I'm on my third glass, so speak slowly.

15:55.372 --> 15:58.625
You know how you and I were both worried
he didn't think this through?

15:58.792 --> 16:00.043
He thought it through.

16:00.210 --> 16:03.254
- It's Damon. He didn't.
<i>- He's ready to do this, Elena.</i>

16:03.421 --> 16:05.382
He's got your perfect life planned out.

16:05.548 --> 16:08.426
I want the perfect human life with him too,
Stefan. Trust me.

16:08.593 --> 16:10.387
But life isn't perfect.

16:10.553 --> 16:13.932
Okay, look, you have a few more hours,
so push him.

16:14.099 --> 16:15.934
<i>Make him see that.</i>

16:25.860 --> 16:26.903
JO:
Hey.

16:27.112 --> 16:29.656
- Remember when you were pacing yourself?
- Heh.

16:29.823 --> 16:32.575
I do. Right before I
told my ex-boyfriend...

16:32.742 --> 16:36.204
...how to get my current boyfriend
to give up hope for our relationship.

16:37.414 --> 16:40.000
What if I made a huge mistake
by taking the cure?

16:40.250 --> 16:43.253
The only mistake you made
was that last glass of champagne.

16:43.420 --> 16:46.297
I'm gonna make some coffee
before you spiral through to China.

16:46.464 --> 16:48.466
Yeah, okay. Heh.

16:50.301 --> 16:51.720
[GASPS]

16:51.886 --> 16:53.096
Whoa.

16:53.263 --> 16:54.514
Jo?

16:55.765 --> 16:57.392
Are you okay? Jo!

16:58.518 --> 17:00.770
Hey, Jo. Jo. No.

17:02.981 --> 17:04.023
Jo?

17:04.273 --> 17:05.775
Jo!

17:11.781 --> 17:13.282
ELENA:
Thanks.

17:15.492 --> 17:17.787
The doctor got the test results back.

17:17.954 --> 17:20.790
The babies are fine. You're fine.
He thinks it was just...

17:20.957 --> 17:25.127
An acute panic attack brought on by stress,
pregnancy and a severe lack of food.

17:25.295 --> 17:26.378
Yeah.

17:26.838 --> 17:30.091
What are the chances of you
being an amazing maid of honor...

17:30.300 --> 17:32.969
...and keeping this mortifying episode
to yourself?

17:33.136 --> 17:34.596
I don't wanna worry Ric.

17:35.138 --> 17:36.973
Of course.

17:39.100 --> 17:41.895
- You can't tell her I told you.
- Fine, but I wanna see her.

17:42.145 --> 17:43.772
- Not until the wedding.
- Elena...

17:43.938 --> 17:47.317
If there's anywhere that you should
be superstitious, it's Mystic Falls.

17:47.525 --> 17:51.321
- Okay, fine. But what happened?
- The doctors think that she had a panic attack.

17:51.488 --> 17:53.990
As in "she doesn't wanna get married"
panic attack? Great.

17:54.157 --> 17:57.619
As in it's her wedding day and she has two
humans growing inside her...

17:57.827 --> 18:00.205
...and can't self-medicate like you,
bourbon breath.

18:01.706 --> 18:03.333
Sorry.

18:03.917 --> 18:08.338
I just... I saw her fall, and my first
instinct was to vamp to her, but I couldn't.

18:08.505 --> 18:12.967
And then I saw her hit her head, and I wanted
to give her vampire blood, but I couldn't.

18:13.384 --> 18:15.678
Wait, so are you having second thoughts?

18:16.054 --> 18:19.140
No, because then I thought,
"What would a human do?"

18:19.349 --> 18:23.228
So I called 911, got her to the hospital,
and then I let the doctors do their job.

18:23.686 --> 18:26.272
And it felt oddly empowering.

18:26.523 --> 18:29.025
- Why didn't you tell me?
- Tell you what?

18:29.192 --> 18:31.569
How amazing it feels to be human again.

18:32.070 --> 18:35.240
At first, I was worried that it might
take the edge off my senses...

18:35.448 --> 18:37.325
...but it's the opposite.

18:37.492 --> 18:39.285
I feel...

18:39.786 --> 18:41.704
...connected to the world again.

18:41.871 --> 18:44.332
- I feel...
- Alive?

18:45.834 --> 18:46.876
Yeah.

18:47.043 --> 18:50.213
That's because your life has purpose again.
It's finite.

18:50.421 --> 18:52.090
And it's...

18:53.550 --> 18:56.386
...pretty much the greatest feeling
in the whole world.

18:56.553 --> 18:58.596
I made you guys some amazing drinks.

18:58.763 --> 19:00.223
With a little bit of tequila.

19:00.390 --> 19:01.891
Okay, a lot of tequila.

19:02.058 --> 19:04.561
And there's only one of you.

19:05.895 --> 19:07.605
- What did you do?
- I didn't do anything.

19:07.772 --> 19:10.608
Ugh. He said angrily.

19:14.904 --> 19:15.989
Nothing has changed.

19:16.239 --> 19:18.783
Because she walks in with a pretty dress
and new haircut...

19:18.950 --> 19:20.285
...I'm supposed to forget how she acted?

19:20.451 --> 19:24.080
No, you're supposed to talk to her
like an adult and work out your problems.

19:24.247 --> 19:26.916
- You don't know about our problems.
- I know about your problems.

19:27.083 --> 19:30.587
Unless you're cool with only making it
two weeks in the police academy...

19:30.753 --> 19:32.422
...and having no purpose in life.

19:32.589 --> 19:35.258
At least when you had her,
you were trying, Tyler.

19:36.759 --> 19:39.387
You're giving me advice
about relationships?

19:39.554 --> 19:41.973
After all your Stefan drama this year?
Do me a favor.

19:42.223 --> 19:44.809
Figure out your own damn life.
Let me worry about mine.

19:47.020 --> 19:48.521
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

19:54.444 --> 19:56.821
Well, I applaud you for
your effort, Stefan...

19:56.988 --> 19:59.991
...but I think it's time
for the "this is your life" tour to end.

20:00.325 --> 20:03.578
- You got the address?
- Yup. Tuxes are in the car. We're good to go.

20:03.745 --> 20:06.164
- Hey, just one more thing.
- Ugh. What now?

20:06.331 --> 20:10.418
You're gonna give me a lecture on laundry?
Oil changes? Personal hygiene?

20:11.544 --> 20:13.922
- Breakups.
- What about them?

20:14.088 --> 20:16.341
I guess you hadn't thought
about that, right?

20:16.507 --> 20:18.760
What if you and Elena
aren't really soul mates?

20:18.968 --> 20:21.888
I'm not big on labels, but I think
we're pretty good on that front.

20:22.055 --> 20:24.515
Ah. You sound like me four years ago.

20:24.766 --> 20:27.518
You know, Elena and me,
we were soul mates too.

20:27.685 --> 20:28.978
Watch it, Stefan.

20:29.479 --> 20:30.855
Hey, I'm just being realistic.

20:31.022 --> 20:34.484
What if something goes wrong?
You're human. Still isolated. Still alone.

20:34.651 --> 20:37.362
- Not gonna happen.
- Right. Couples stay together forever.

20:37.528 --> 20:41.366
They never fight, they never hurt
each other, they never drift apart.

20:41.532 --> 20:43.660
- Hmm.
- Let me show you.

20:44.619 --> 20:45.954
[DAMON GRUNTS]

20:46.621 --> 20:48.498
[DOOR OPENS]

20:51.501 --> 20:52.669
[DOOR CLOSES]

20:55.505 --> 20:57.215
You're still up.

20:58.174 --> 20:59.717
Rough night?

20:59.926 --> 21:02.679
Just long.

21:03.304 --> 21:05.014
I keep having to tell myself...

21:05.181 --> 21:08.726
...a couple of more years of residency,
and I'll be free.

21:08.935 --> 21:10.603
Come sit, have a drink with me.

21:10.853 --> 21:14.190
I'm actually kind of tired.
I'm gonna go to bed.

21:17.860 --> 21:19.112
[ELENA YAWNS]

21:24.617 --> 21:27.578
Oh, God, Elena has a job.
Somebody help me.

21:27.745 --> 21:30.206
That's just two years in.
Wait till you hit seven.

21:36.045 --> 21:38.256
Mm. Hello.

21:39.882 --> 21:41.551
You're drunk.

21:42.719 --> 21:44.595
I sense judgment.

21:44.846 --> 21:47.557
Which is odd.
You're the one that wanted me to own a bar.

21:47.724 --> 21:51.936
I wanted you to own it, Damon,
not pass out on it every night.

21:52.729 --> 21:55.231
Well, that bar is a lot more affectionate
than you.

21:56.983 --> 21:58.192
[ELENA SCOFFS]

21:58.359 --> 22:02.405
I just finished my residency, Damon.
I'm working my butt off to build a career.

22:02.572 --> 22:05.283
Well, I'm drinking my
butt off building mine.

22:05.450 --> 22:08.828
- If you're that unhappy, then just sell the bar.
- And do what?

22:08.995 --> 22:11.748
I don't care, Damon.
Whatever it is you wanna do.

22:11.914 --> 22:13.374
Well, that's the thing, Elena.

22:13.583 --> 22:15.626
I can't do what I wanna do.

22:15.793 --> 22:18.921
Because what I wanna do is drink all night
without getting drunk...

22:19.088 --> 22:20.715
...drive my car like a psycho...

22:20.882 --> 22:22.216
...without fear of death.

22:22.383 --> 22:25.595
I wanna tear someone's head off
without getting arrested.

22:25.762 --> 22:28.264
You're right.
You can't do any of those things anymore.

22:28.431 --> 22:29.640
Because of you.

22:30.099 --> 22:32.185
I can't because of you.

22:32.810 --> 22:34.437
Just say it.

22:35.688 --> 22:38.232
- This was a damn mistake.
- You're right.

22:39.192 --> 22:40.526
This was a mistake.

22:42.570 --> 22:43.654
[GLASS SHATTERS]

22:43.821 --> 22:45.156
Get out of my head!

22:47.992 --> 22:50.286
I see what you're doing.

22:50.703 --> 22:52.497
This isn't about me being alone.

22:52.663 --> 22:54.248
This is about you being alone.

22:54.415 --> 22:57.293
Without me, without Elena.

22:57.460 --> 22:59.462
Awfully selfish of you, brother.

22:59.629 --> 23:02.965
Even if you and Elena
defy every single statistic...

23:03.132 --> 23:05.551
...and stay in love every
hour of every day...

23:07.136 --> 23:09.847
...you still can't control life or death.

23:10.014 --> 23:12.016
She's human. She could die at any moment.

23:12.183 --> 23:15.144
What is your life
gonna look like without her?

23:47.176 --> 23:49.178
[MICROWAVE HUMMING]

24:09.198 --> 24:11.200
[MICROWAVE BEEPING]

24:12.118 --> 24:15.872
MAN [ON TV]: <i>I just love prosciutto
and melon. It couldn't be any more simple.</i>

24:16.038 --> 24:18.541
<i>I do have my own kind of way...</i>

24:18.708 --> 24:23.254
<i>...of serving it that is a little
nontraditional, but as long as no one tells...</i>

24:23.504 --> 24:25.131
<i>...I won't be in trouble.</i>

24:25.381 --> 24:28.759
<i>What I'm gonna do is clean out
the center of that melon. It is so easy...</i>

24:47.445 --> 24:49.280
So you make us drift apart.

24:50.907 --> 24:52.742
Break us up and then kill her.

24:54.911 --> 24:57.747
- That's harsh, brother.
- She wanted me to be harsh.

25:00.583 --> 25:01.834
This was her idea too?

25:02.251 --> 25:03.461
Well, that's funny.

25:04.587 --> 25:07.548
Because the two people closest to me
are the two most sadistic.

25:09.759 --> 25:12.094
If you do this, Damon,
you're human forever.

25:12.261 --> 25:15.932
No matter what happens,
there's no going back.

25:20.686 --> 25:22.563
What do you think I should do?

25:22.730 --> 25:24.607
That's the thing. I can't tell you.

25:24.815 --> 25:26.567
Elena can't tell you.

25:26.734 --> 25:29.487
You can't do this for me or for her.

25:29.654 --> 25:33.074
You have to want to be human for yourself.

25:44.752 --> 25:46.128
- Champagne?
- Oh, yes.

25:50.132 --> 25:54.637
Oh, excuse me. They need
some more drinks over there. Thank you.

25:55.638 --> 25:58.474
- Hey, where's Jo? Is she...?
- She's fine. They discharged her.

25:58.641 --> 26:00.351
There's a back entrance she can use.

26:00.518 --> 26:02.562
- It avoids being seen.
- Okay. I'll tell her.

26:02.728 --> 26:05.398
- Great. Hmm?
- Stefan.

26:07.650 --> 26:09.443
I'm gonna go wait for Jo.

26:09.610 --> 26:10.903
Okay.

26:11.988 --> 26:13.781
I'm not used to scaring people away.

26:13.948 --> 26:16.409
People are uncomfortable
around Salvatores in tuxes.

26:16.576 --> 26:17.743
It stirs...

26:17.910 --> 26:19.537
...feelings.
STEFAN: Uh-oh.

26:19.704 --> 26:22.331
Elena's human again.
Am I sensing another brother swap?

26:22.498 --> 26:24.166
[ELENA LAUGHS]

26:25.126 --> 26:26.210
Is he with you?

26:26.377 --> 26:28.588
No, he needed some time to think.

26:28.754 --> 26:30.298
That sounds very ominous.

26:33.175 --> 26:35.052
You don't want him to take it, do you?

26:35.219 --> 26:36.679
Oh, it's not up to me.

26:36.846 --> 26:39.724
Stefan, I'm not him.
You can tell me how you really feel.

26:40.683 --> 26:43.728
Look, of course I don't want him
to take it. He's my brother.

26:44.020 --> 26:46.105
The thought of losing him is...

26:46.272 --> 26:47.648
Yeah, I know.

26:49.275 --> 26:51.068
So, what do you think he's gonna do?

26:52.194 --> 26:55.156
Well, you never knew Damon as a human.

26:55.323 --> 26:58.701
<i>He was aimless.
Always searching for something more.</i>

26:58.868 --> 27:01.162
<i>Sweet and earnest. To a fault.</i>

27:01.871 --> 27:03.456
<i>But never strong.</i>

27:06.917 --> 27:08.753
[BALL BOUNCING]

27:11.589 --> 27:15.301
STEFAN:
<i>That came later. When he found himself.</i>

27:15.801 --> 27:17.219
<i>When he truly became Damon.</i>

27:19.221 --> 27:21.015
<i>He loves being a vampire.</i>

27:22.058 --> 27:24.977
<i>And I just don't think
he'll ever give that up.</i>

27:26.729 --> 27:30.149
- She's gonna kill us.
- The point is so we were in control of her.

27:30.358 --> 27:33.235
Not Lily. Caroline.
The wedding starts in an hour.

27:33.402 --> 27:36.364
All we have to do is knock her ass out
and drag her to the boiler room.

27:36.530 --> 27:38.199
Thirty minutes, tops.

27:42.244 --> 27:43.579
Bonnie.

27:46.082 --> 27:47.917
Enzo must have let her out.

27:48.167 --> 27:49.585
We have to warn everyone.

27:51.712 --> 27:53.297
[MATT GASPING]

27:56.092 --> 27:58.010
- Matt?
- I...

27:58.177 --> 27:59.679
- What's wrong?
- I can't breathe.

27:59.845 --> 28:02.932
- It's like someone's crushing my throat.
- Just hang on. I'll...

28:03.099 --> 28:04.684
[GASPING]

28:19.407 --> 28:20.449
LILY:
Tea, please.

28:20.658 --> 28:22.410
Earl Grey.

28:26.664 --> 28:28.249
To what do I owe the pleasure?

28:28.416 --> 28:32.503
I heard you tried to bring me something
called an MP3 player.

28:32.920 --> 28:36.966
I'm not entirely sure what that is,
but still, I wanted to thank you.

28:37.133 --> 28:39.760
And they let you out of
your cell to do this?

28:39.927 --> 28:42.638
Of course not, but I'm resourceful.

28:45.307 --> 28:46.934
Should I be concerned...

28:47.143 --> 28:49.645
...about an imminent Ripper binge?
LILY: Actually, no.

28:49.812 --> 28:51.188
You shouldn't.

28:51.397 --> 28:55.192
I was a Ripper because I lost my family.

28:55.401 --> 28:58.195
But today I'm getting them back.

29:03.325 --> 29:04.952
[CELL PHONE BUZZING]

29:08.247 --> 29:11.767
- If you're trying to organize a rendezvous...
ALARIC [OVER PHONE]: <i>Don't worry. I'm not.</i>

29:11.917 --> 29:13.711
I just need help with my vows.

29:13.878 --> 29:15.629
What rhymes with "battlefield clamp"?

29:15.796 --> 29:17.339
- Divorce.
<i>- Ha, ha.</i>

29:17.506 --> 29:18.674
<i>So how are yours coming?</i>

29:18.841 --> 29:20.885
Stop fishing for spoilers.

29:21.051 --> 29:24.805
You know, this place is crawling with
Gemini. Who knew there were so many of you?

29:24.972 --> 29:28.768
Well, there's not much to do in the coven
other than procreate.

29:29.602 --> 29:32.605
- You haven't seen my dad, have you?
<i>- No, actually.</i>

29:32.772 --> 29:35.524
But it's big of you
to invite your attempted murderer.

29:35.691 --> 29:37.818
He gives really good gifts.

29:37.985 --> 29:40.362
Oh, and never say "big of you"
to a pregnant woman.

29:40.529 --> 29:41.655
[CHUCKLES]

29:42.239 --> 29:44.158
I hate that I can't see you right now.

29:45.618 --> 29:47.369
I love that you hate it.

29:47.536 --> 29:49.705
<i>- I'll see you soon.</i>
- Bye.

29:51.248 --> 29:55.336
Maybe I should just, uh,
leave my gift and go, then?

29:57.546 --> 30:00.174
Dad. What are you doing back here?

30:00.674 --> 30:02.176
You're my daughter.

30:02.343 --> 30:03.677
And I, um... Ahem.

30:04.261 --> 30:06.555
I don't expect you to say yes...

30:07.765 --> 30:11.352
...but if I didn't at least ask
to walk you down the aisle...

30:11.560 --> 30:13.229
...I couldn't live with myself.

30:21.779 --> 30:23.531
You're avoiding me.

30:24.532 --> 30:27.660
What? No, I'm not avoiding you.

30:27.827 --> 30:31.747
I'm trying to organize this whole circus
here. Did you see where they put the bar?

30:31.914 --> 30:33.415
Caroline...

30:34.083 --> 30:35.334
...can we talk?

30:39.004 --> 30:40.644
STEFAN:
All right, just say it. I'm wrong.

30:40.714 --> 30:43.194
- I'm making this about me. I'm
being selfish. CAROLINE: Sorry.

30:43.342 --> 30:47.221
Not wanting to lose your brother
is pretty low on the selfish scale.

30:48.764 --> 30:53.185
Now, forcing someone to turn off
their humanity, on the other hand, that...

30:53.352 --> 30:56.772
Mm. Yeah, that's, uh...
That's way up there.

30:56.939 --> 30:58.649
CAROLINE:
Yeah.

31:04.405 --> 31:05.447
Do you hate me?

31:05.614 --> 31:10.995
No, of course I don't hate you. Doesn't mean
that I don't hate the way you handled things.

31:11.161 --> 31:13.163
Yeah, well, that makes two of us.

31:17.376 --> 31:18.752
I made a list...

31:20.254 --> 31:24.341
...of, um, all the things that I've done
since I fell for you.

31:25.759 --> 31:28.053
It started last summer,
when you moved away.

31:28.554 --> 31:31.223
I started obsessing over where you were...

31:31.390 --> 31:33.270
...wondering why you weren't returning
my calls.

31:33.392 --> 31:35.728
I told you I hated you
when I felt ignored...

31:35.895 --> 31:38.647
...missed my mom's final moments
because I was kissing you.

31:38.814 --> 31:40.608
- And then she died.
- Caroline...

31:40.774 --> 31:45.738
And all I needed was for you to tell me
that you felt something for me...

31:47.197 --> 31:49.241
...and you didn't.

31:49.783 --> 31:50.826
And it affected me...

31:51.035 --> 31:55.497
...so deeply that I did
the worst possible thing a vampire can do.

31:55.706 --> 31:57.541
I turned off my humanity.

31:57.708 --> 32:02.296
And when I thought I couldn't do
anything else, I got you to turn off yours.

32:05.424 --> 32:06.926
Well, I forgive you.

32:07.092 --> 32:09.136
Yeah, but that's the point, Stefan.

32:09.345 --> 32:11.388
The old Caroline wouldn't have forgiven me.

32:11.555 --> 32:15.059
She would've smacked me and said,
"What the hell are you doing?"

32:16.727 --> 32:20.147
I hate the way that this has made me feel.

32:20.314 --> 32:22.441
You're a control freak who's lost control.

32:22.816 --> 32:25.027
I feel the same way when I'm around you.

32:25.194 --> 32:27.655
That's what falling for somebody is.

32:27.988 --> 32:30.240
It's being vulnerable.

32:30.783 --> 32:31.909
It's...

32:33.452 --> 32:35.621
...giving up control.

32:38.874 --> 32:39.917
CAROLINE:
I know.

32:43.629 --> 32:46.840
But where I'm at right now in my life...

32:47.007 --> 32:52.096
...with the guilt and the grief,
control is all I have.

32:54.098 --> 32:57.059
And I don't think that I can give that up.

33:23.919 --> 33:25.004
H i.

33:25.170 --> 33:28.382
Isn't a bridesmaid's dress supposed
to make you look like a freak of nature?

33:28.549 --> 33:29.883
[CHUCKLES]

33:30.467 --> 33:33.095
- Jo went easy on me.
- Hmm.

33:37.057 --> 33:38.809
I talked to Stefan.

33:39.935 --> 33:42.104
He did not go easy on me.

33:42.271 --> 33:44.398
Apparently that's your fault.

33:44.565 --> 33:47.401
His argument was pretty convincing.

33:49.111 --> 33:50.571
I'd made up my mind.

33:52.740 --> 33:54.324
But then...

33:54.533 --> 33:56.618
You ruined my ball.

33:56.785 --> 33:58.912
You're lucky I didn't ruin your face.

33:59.079 --> 34:02.416
Go inside, get the car keys
from your mommy. I'm going to a wedding.

34:09.630 --> 34:11.967
On second thought...

34:12.676 --> 34:14.636
- Don't forget the...
- The leftovers.

34:14.844 --> 34:17.306
I know. You told me three times.

34:17.473 --> 34:19.308
Forty years, and every time:

34:19.516 --> 34:21.435
"Did you remember the leftovers?"

34:21.601 --> 34:24.103
Like I'm getting senile or something. Oh.

34:28.567 --> 34:29.985
Heh.

34:43.706 --> 34:44.833
Heh.

34:47.043 --> 34:48.087
I'm taking it.

34:49.338 --> 34:52.382
I've been a vampire for a long time, Elena.

34:52.882 --> 34:54.426
And it's been a blast.

34:54.802 --> 34:57.513
But I would give it up in a second
to be your husband...

34:58.055 --> 34:59.765
...your partner...

35:00.140 --> 35:02.351
...the father of your kids.

35:04.311 --> 35:05.813
You can't take it just for me.

35:05.979 --> 35:10.067
That's what you and Stefan keep saying,
but you're wrong. I can.

35:10.943 --> 35:12.861
I can take it for us.

35:14.321 --> 35:16.824
Okay? Because even if it doesn't work...

35:17.032 --> 35:20.410
...even if it all goes to hell,
even if I'm miserable and alone...

35:20.619 --> 35:24.331
...the smallest chance
at the perfect life with you...

35:24.665 --> 35:27.417
...is infinitely better
than an immortal one without you.

35:29.795 --> 35:33.757
And I know this, Elena. I love you.

35:35.425 --> 35:39.555
And I will love you
until I take my last breath on this Earth.

36:07.040 --> 36:08.458
CAROLINE:
Where the hell are you?

36:08.709 --> 36:10.919
Bonnie and Matt are MIA,
and now you and Damon?

36:11.128 --> 36:13.088
What is wrong with you?
This is a wedding.

36:13.255 --> 36:16.466
This is supposed to be Jo's magical night,
and you are ruining it.

36:16.717 --> 36:18.844
We're starting without you.

36:19.011 --> 36:21.013
[JO LAUGHING]

36:23.473 --> 36:25.100
This is not funny.

36:25.350 --> 36:29.104
- It's kind of funny.
- I don't wanna tell you how to run a wedding...

36:29.271 --> 36:31.899
We're not waiting anymore.
Tell them to cue the music.

36:48.207 --> 36:50.209
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING IN DISTANCE]

36:51.293 --> 36:52.586
Um...

36:52.753 --> 36:53.962
I think it's starting.

36:54.129 --> 36:56.965
What? No. What time is it?

36:58.300 --> 36:59.384
Oh, my God.

36:59.593 --> 37:01.929
No, no, no. We're so late.

37:02.137 --> 37:05.140
- You couldn't keep your paws off of me.
- Damon.

37:05.307 --> 37:06.475
Put your tux back on.

37:06.683 --> 37:09.144
I am. I am. Ha, ha.

37:13.440 --> 37:14.483
I hope it was worth it.

37:14.691 --> 37:16.485
- Actually...
- Ugh, gross. Not the time.

37:16.693 --> 37:18.153
Have you seen Bonnie or Matt?

37:18.320 --> 37:19.988
- They're not here yet?
- Just go.

37:20.197 --> 37:22.032
- Go, go, go.
- Okay.

37:31.166 --> 37:32.668
[GRUNTS]

37:40.008 --> 37:41.551
Bonnie?

37:43.929 --> 37:45.430
Bonnie?

37:46.431 --> 37:47.516
Hey.

37:53.313 --> 37:54.982
It was...

37:59.361 --> 38:00.696
And so?

38:01.863 --> 38:04.366
DAMON:
Looks like I'm joining the human club.

38:04.533 --> 38:06.076
It's a big night for both of us.

38:06.660 --> 38:09.037
- I'm proud of you.
- You too, buddy.

39:00.255 --> 39:03.967
Welcome family and friends
on this magical evening...

39:04.134 --> 39:08.889
...to the wedding of Alaric Saltzman
and Josette Laughlin.

39:09.097 --> 39:11.475
Josette and Alaric
have prepared their own vows.

39:16.688 --> 39:17.898
[ALARIC CLEARS THROAT]

39:23.278 --> 39:25.947
This can't be it. No one's here.

39:26.156 --> 39:29.034
Perhaps your companions
gave you the wrong address.

39:31.411 --> 39:34.122
They're not the ones
who gave me the address.

39:35.123 --> 39:36.958
Then who did?

39:39.127 --> 39:41.671
ALARIC:
<i>Neither one of us should be here right now.</i>

39:42.297 --> 39:44.591
We've spent our lives dodging fate...

39:45.467 --> 39:47.010
...and beating the odds.

39:49.054 --> 39:52.099
But because we did...

39:53.266 --> 39:55.018
...I got to meet you...

39:55.477 --> 39:57.854
...the most beautiful...

39:58.563 --> 40:03.568
...hilarious and intimidatingly
brilliant woman...

40:03.777 --> 40:05.821
...I have ever known.

40:06.822 --> 40:08.990
You inspire me.

40:09.157 --> 40:11.451
You've shown me that happiness...

40:11.660 --> 40:15.038
...is actually something
that I can have in my life.

40:18.166 --> 40:19.751
And so...

40:23.505 --> 40:26.508
...I promise to be with you...

40:27.092 --> 40:29.010
...and love you...

40:29.177 --> 40:31.555
...and to dodge fate with you...

40:33.723 --> 40:35.809
...for the rest of our lives.

40:44.860 --> 40:46.653
REVEREND:
Josette?

40:47.237 --> 40:48.488
Oh, God.

40:48.697 --> 40:50.115
That's a tough act to follow.

40:50.282 --> 40:51.700
[ALL LAUGH]

40:51.867 --> 40:53.702
Here goes.

40:54.703 --> 40:56.705
Alaric Saltzman...

40:56.872 --> 40:57.914
...you are...

40:58.081 --> 40:59.207
[FLESH TEARING]

40:59.749 --> 41:01.751
Jo? What is it?

41:02.002 --> 41:03.044
Jo... Oh, my God.

41:03.253 --> 41:04.629
Jo?

41:07.048 --> 41:08.133
Oh, God, no.

41:08.341 --> 41:09.634
JO: No!
- No, no, no.

41:09.801 --> 41:11.470
[JO SCREAMS & ELENA GASPS]

41:12.387 --> 41:15.849
Oh, my God! No, no, no. Jo.

41:16.057 --> 41:20.228
I was gonna wait till the "death do us part"
bit, but it seemed a little on the nose.

41:21.271 --> 41:22.397
No.

41:23.398 --> 41:24.983
Am I right?

41:26.276 --> 41:28.236
[RINGING & CROWD SCREAMING]

41:33.575 --> 41:34.743
Miss me?

41:37.454 --> 41:39.080
No?

41:40.040 --> 41:41.875
Oh, well.

42:22.499 --> 42:24.501
[English - US - SDH]
